The bank at southwest China's Giant Panda Protection and Research Centre in the Wolong Nature Reserve in Sichuan province will be completed this year.
China has applied to the United Nations to make giant pandas' natural habitat in southwestern Sichuan province a world heritage area to help protect the endangered species.
Currently more than 1,500 giant pandas live wild in China, according to a survey by the State Forestry Administration.
China will soon finish building its first blood bank for pandas.
